83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
Enrolled
Senate Concurrent Resolution 207
Sponsored by Senator WAGNER (Presession filed.)
Be It Resolved by the Legislative Assembly of the State of Oregon:
(1) This resolution constitutes a rule of proceeding of the Senate and the House of Represen-
tatives of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly.
(2) The Senate and the House of Representatives shall adhere to the following schedule and
deadlines for the 2026 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly:
(a) The Senate and the House of Representatives shall convene in regular session on February
2, 2026.
(b) Committee chairpersons shall schedule work sessions for measures in the chamber of origin
no later than February 9, 2026. This paragraph does not apply to:
(A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
(B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, Joint Committee
on Transportation Funding and Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
(C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
Committee on Rules, House Committee on Rules, Senate Committee on Conduct and House Com-
mittee on Conduct.
(c) Committees shall consider measures in the chamber of origin no later than February 16, 2026.
This paragraph does not apply to:
(A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
(B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, Joint Committee
on Transportation Funding and Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
(C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
Committee on Rules, House Committee on Rules, Senate Committee on Conduct and House Com-
mittee on Conduct.
(d) Committee chairpersons shall schedule work sessions for measures in the second chamber
no later than February 20, 2026. This paragraph does not apply to:
(A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
(B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, the Joint Com-
mittee on Transportation Funding and the Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
(C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
Committee on Rules, House Committee on Rules, Senate Committee on Conduct and House Com-
mittee on Conduct.
(e) Committees shall consider measures in the second chamber no later than February 26, 2026.
This paragraph does not apply to:
(A) The Joint Committee on Ways and Means;
(B) Other joint committees except for the Joint Committee on Transportation, the Joint Com-
mittee on Transportation Funding and the Joint Committee on Transportation Oversight; and
(C) The Senate Committee on Finance and Revenue, House Committee on Revenue, Senate
Committee on Rules, House Committee on Rules, Senate Committee on Conduct and House Com-
mittee on Conduct.
